List the coordinates in order: \(D(0, 3)\), \(B(0, 0)\), \(E(4, 0)\), \(F\left(\frac{8}{3}, 2\right)\), and back to \(D(0, 3)\). 2. Apply the shoelace formula: \[ \text{Area} = \frac{1}{2} \left| \sum_{i=1}^{n} (x_i y_{i+1} - y_i x_{i+1}) \right| \] 3. Calculate the sums: \[ \begin{aligned} &\text{Sum of } x_i y_{i+1}: 0 \cdot 0 + 0 \cdot 0 + 4 \cdot 2 + \frac{8}{3} \cdot 3 + 0 \cdot 3 = 0 + 0 + 8 + 8 + 0 = 16, \\ &\text{Sum of } y_i x_{i+1}: 3 \cdot 0 + 0 \cdot 4 + 0 \cdot \frac{8}{3} + 2 \cdot 0 + 3 \cdot 0 = 0 + 0 + 0 + 0 + 0 = 0. \end{aligned} \] 4. Compute the area: \[ \text{Area} = \frac{1}{2} \left| 16 - 0 \right| = \frac{1}{2} \times 16 = 8. \] Thus, the area of quadrilateral \(DBEF\) is \(\boxed{8}\).
